On International Holocaust Remembrance Day, the President and First Lady express their commitment to remembering the six million Jews and millions of others who were killed by the Nazis. They pledge to keep their memories alive through their actions and speak out against Holocaust denial. They also vow to stand against all forms of hatred and atrocities, including the resurgence of anti-Semitism. They draw inspiration from those who risked their lives to save others and pledge to continue working towards repairing the world. They join with Israel and friends around the world in dedicating themselves to the words "Never Forget. Never Again."